For this one, we dont need to check_if_X_in_A. We just need to generate a bunch of \(X\)s. We can still use the same code

# Bernoulli:
pseq = seq(.01,.99,len = 100)
GeometricMean = rep(NA, 100)
for(i in 1:100){
  GeometricMean[i] = rgeom(10000,pseq[i]) %>% mean
}

plot(pseq, GeometricMean)

plot((1/pseq)-1, 
     GeometricMean, 
     log = "xy")
abline(0,1)
